      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' The structure of the fBitFields field."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' FieldName             Bit #     Description"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' -----------------     -----     ------------------------------"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fBinary                 1       Windows does not support nonbinary mode transfers, so this member must be =1."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fParity                 2       If =1, parity checking is performed and errors are reported"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fOutxCtsFlow            3       If =1 and CTS is turned off, output is suspended until CTS is sent again."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fOutxDsrFlow            4       If =1 and DSR is turned off, output is suspended until DSR is sent again."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fDtrControl             5,6     DTR flow control (2 bits)"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fDsrSensitivity         7       The driver ignores any bytes received, unless the DSR modem input line is high."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fTXContinueOnXoff       8       XOFF continues Tx"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fOutX                   9       If =1, TX stops when the XoffChar character is received and starts again when the XonChar character is received."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fInX                   10       Indicates whether XON/XOFF flow control is used during reception."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fErrorChar             11       Indicates whether bytes received with parity errors are replaced with the character specified by the ErrorChar."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fNull                  12       If =1, null bytes are discarded when received."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fRtsControl            13,14    RTS flow control (2 bits)"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fAbortOnError          15       If =1, the driver terminates all I/O operations with an error status if an error occurs."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "' fDummy2                16       reserved"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'---------fBitFields-------------"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
